        },
        "body": "Closes #28814\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nThis PR fixes a TypeScript regression in Prisma Client where `accelerateUrl` was incorrectly marked as required in [PrismaClientOptions](cci:2://file:///Users/anirudhpanigrahy/Desktop/PR/prisma/packages/client/src/runtime/getPrismaClient.ts:92:0-150:1) when the `adapter` option was not provided. This caused valid configurations, such as `new PrismaClient({ log: ['query'] })`, to fail type checking.\r\n\r\nThe fix updates [PrismaClientMutuallyExclusiveOptions](cci:2://file:///Users/anirudhpanigrahy/Desktop/PR/prisma/packages/client/src/runtime/getPrismaClient.ts:72:0-90:3) to explicitly allow a case where neither `adapter` nor `accelerateUrl` is present, restoring support for standard client options.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- Modified `packages/client/src/runtime/getPrismaClient.ts` to add a union member to `PrismaClientMutuallyExclusiveOptions`:\r\n  ```ts\r\n  | {\r\n      adapter?: never\r\n      accelerateUrl?: never\r\n    }\n\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\n\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\n\n* **New Features**\n  * Enhanced Prisma Client configuration options to allow omitting both adapter and accelerateUrl settings, providing greater flexibility in client initialization.\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can customize this high-level summary in your review settings.</sub>\n\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
